  "prompt": "Which is best IIT in India?",
  "response": "The **Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs)** are among the most prestigious engineering institutions in India, and determining the \"best\" IIT often depends on various factors such as academic excellence, research output, placements, infrastructure, and reputation. While rankings may vary slightly across different surveys, here are some of the top IITs consistently regarded as the best:\n\n1. **IIT Bombay** - Located in Mumbai, it is often considered the top IIT due to its strong academic programs, research facilities, and placement records. It has a vibrant campus life and collaborations with top global institutions.\n\n2. **IIT Delhi** - Known for its research contributions and industry connections, IIT Delhi is a close competitor to IIT Bombay. It excels in engineering, technology, and entrepreneurship.\n\n3. **IIT Madras** - Located in Chennai, it is renowned for its academic rigor, innovation, and research output. It has a strong focus on interdisciplinary studies and has produced many successful entrepreneurs.\n\n4. **IIT Kanpur** - Known for its emphasis on research and development, IIT Kanpur has a strong reputation in aerospace, computer science, and engineering disciplines.\n\n5. **IIT Kharagpur** - The oldest IIT, it has a massive campus and offers a wide range of programs. It is particularly strong in core engineering fields and has a rich history of academic excellence.\n\n6. **IIT Roorkee** - Known for its civil engineering and infrastructure-related programs, IIT Roorkee is one of the oldest technical institutions in India.\n\n7. **IIT Guwahati** - It has gained prominence in recent years for its research and academic contributions, particularly in the fields of biotechnology and chemical engineering.\n\n### Key Factors to Consider:\n- **Placements**: IIT Bombay and IIT Delhi often lead in terms of the highest packages and placement percentages.\n- **Research**: IIT Madras and IIT Kanpur are known for their strong research culture.\n- **Alumni Network**: IIT Bombay and IIT Delhi have a vast and influential alumni network.\n- **Rankings**: Rankings like NIRF, QS, and Times Higher Education can provide insights, but they may vary slightly.\n\nUltimately, the \"best\" IIT for you depends on your specific interests, career goals, and the field of study you wish to pursue. All IITs offer world-class education and opportunities, so choosing the right one should align with your personal and professional aspirations.",
